ts  or canceling and receiving a refund  is 1 August 2015  COL Jeff Boobar  Superintendent s Liaison to the Parents Council  is the coordinator for this event and he can be contacted for additional information at  540  464 7072 or BoobarJR vmi edu  Saturday  22 August NOTE  Parents should give their cadets spending money  credit cards  checkbooks  etc  prior to going to Cameron Hall for the beginning of the 2 00 Superintendent s Welcome Ceremony  Matriculation Day 7 30 a m    11 30 a m  Cameron Hall Matriculation Fair 8 00 a m    1 00 p m Crozet Hall  Mess Hall   Top Floor  Various VMI agencies  local bankers  local ministers and representatives from several other organizations will be present from the VMI community    Superintendent s Welcome 2 00 p m  Cameron Hall New cadets and their parents will be welcomed by VMI s Superintendent  General J H  Binford Peay  III  62 and introduced to the Dean of Faculty  the Commandant of Cadets  the Co President of the VMI Parents Council  and the Class Advisor  New cadets leave their families following the ceremony to begin their nine day cadre period  March Off Approximately 2 30 p m  Cameron Hall New cadets leave their families and are formed into companies inside Cameron Hall to begin their nine day cadre training period  Family and friends may stay to watch the march off in Cameron Hall  Finish for the day 3 00 p m   No friends or family members are allowed in barracks after the 2 30 March Off in Cameron Hall  Two weeks after matriculation New Cadet Oath Ceremony  Sunday  6 September  11 00 a m  New Market Battlefield State Historical Park in New Market  VA  New Cadets will take a historic tour and recite the Cadet Oath  They will charge across the battlefield exactly as the New Market cadets did on May 15  1864  Following the formal events  cadets will be able to enjoy a picnic lunch with their families and friends  If desired box lunches can be ordered from the Parents Council Table at Matriculation  Events conclude with a parade through town after lunch  Cadets must return to Post on VMI buses  but will be able to sign out to spend time that evening with their parents in Lexington  All new cadets must return to Post no later than 10 00 p m  More information about the New Cadet Oath Ceremony and Parade VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI  RESOURCES   Title IX  Health   Safety   IT   Site Index Parents   Families   Cadets   Non discrimination Statement   Privacy   THE VMI PHILOSOPHY The VMI experience is framed by relevant education within a military environment  It s an education that develops character  fosters a lifelong appreciation of physical fitness engenders a sense of responsibility to others  and cultivates the ability to master adversity  VIRGINIA MILITARY INSTITUTE Lexington  Virginia 24450 General Information   540  464 7230  Admissions  admissions vmi edu skip to content VMI VMI Foundation Keydet Club Alumni Webcams Directories My VMI Menu About About Us Administrative Offices Institute Report News  Photos  Videos VMI Archives Museums VMI Museum System The VMI Museum New Market Battlefield Stonewall Jackson House For Visitors Directions   Map Employment Parents   Family Conferences Chessie Nature Trail Bookstore Resources MyVMI Directories Friendly URLs Post View Health and Safety Computing Academics Areas of Study Majors   Minors Arts   Humanities Engineering Information   Social Sciences Life Sciences Natural Sciences ROTC Enrichment Institute Honors Program International Programs Service Opportunities Summer Programs Institute Writing Program Research Support Cadet Counseling Career Services Disabilities Services Miller Academic Center Advising Math Resource Center The Writing Center Resources Registrar Financial Aid Canvas Login Dean s Office Career Services Bookstore Cadet Computing Admissions Corps Life Athletics Library   Archives Preston Library Library Home Find Books Departments Media Equipment Technical Services Visitor Information A