erintendent  General J H  Binford Peay  III  62 and introduced to the Dean of Faculty  the Commandant of Cadets  the Co President of the VMI Parents Council  and the Class Advisor  New cadets leave their families following the ceremony to begin their nine day cadre period  March Off Approximately 2 30 p m  Cameron Hall New cadets leave their families and are formed into companies inside Cameron Hall to begin their nine day cadre training period  Family and friends may stay to watch the march off in Cameron Hall  Finish for the day 3 00 p m   No friends or family members are allowed in barracks after the 2 30 March Off in Cameron Hall  Two weeks after matriculation New Cadet Oath Ceremony  Sunday  6 September  11 00 a m  New Market Battlefield State Historical Park in New Market  VA  New Cadets will take a historic tour and recite the Cadet Oath  They will charge across the battlefield exactly as the New Market cadets did on May 15  1864  Following the formal events  cadets will be able to enjoy a picnic lunch with their families and friends  If desired box lunches can be ordered from the Parents Council Table at Matriculation  Events conclude with a parade through town after lunch  Cadets must return to Post on VMI buses  but will be able to sign out to spend time that evening with their parents in Lexington  All new cadets must return to Post no later than 10 00 p m  More information about the New Cadet Oath Ceremony and Parade General Information Events Directions What you need to bring Matriculation Details Especially for parents  New Cadet Oath Ceremony Frequently Asked Questions Matriculation Day Brochure Katrina Butner Office Manager P   540  464 7104 F   540  464 7660 Email the Office 201 Smith Hall Virginia Military Institute Lexington  VA  2445  General Information Events Directions What you need to bring Matriculation Details Especially for parents  New Cadet Oath Ceremony Frequently Asked Questions Matriculation Day Brochure Katrina Butner Office Manager 